{"node_id": "c30c5a05", "title": "Data steps", "path": "thinking-in-langgraph > Thinking in LangGraph > Step 2: Identify what each step needs to do > Data steps", "content": "When a step needs to retrieve information from external sources:\n\n<AccordionGroup>\n  <Accordion title=\"Document search\">\n    * Parameters: Query built from intent and topic\n    * Retry strategy: Yes, with exponential backoff for transient failures\n    * Caching: Could cache common queries to reduce API calls\n  </Accordion>\n\n  <Accordion title=\"Customer history lookup\">\n    * Parameters: Customer email or ID from state\n    * Retry strategy: Yes, but with fallback to basic info if unavailable\n    * Caching: Yes, with time-to-live to balance freshness and performance\n  </Accordion>\n</AccordionGroup>", "summary": "Describes data retrieval steps in LangGraph, including document search and customer history lookup, detailing parameters, retry strategies, and caching mechanisms.", "keywords": ["Document search", "Customer history lookup", "Parameters", "Retry strategy", "Caching", "Exponential backoff", "Time-to-live", "API calls", "State", "Query"]}